# Indah Machine Website

Product catalog site for indahmachine.com — machinery distributor in Medan, Indonesia.

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Astro (static export) + Tailwind CSS
- Hosting: **GitHub Pages** via **GitHub Actions** (`.github/workflows/deploy-pages.yml`) — publishes `website/absolute-astronaut/dist/`. Optional later: **Custom domain** in repo Pages settings + DNS (`CNAME` → `www.indahmachine.com`); until then use the default `*.github.io` URL only.
- i18n: URL-based routing — `/en/` and `/id/` with `hreflang` meta tags on every page
- Root `/` redirects to browser language preference (fallback: `/en/`)
- Pricing policy: contact-for-quote only (no public price list)
- Service scope: installation, commissioning, and technical advisory if needed

## Project Structure
```
website/absolute-astronaut/  # Astro app (npm run build → dist/)
scripts/                     # sync-public-assets.js, merge-products.js, translate-to-id.js
.github/workflows/         # deploy-pages.yml (CI)
product_input/             # Draft CSVs — may be inaccurate, validate before use
raw_catalog/               # Source-of-truth PDFs (synced into site public/ on build)
base44_product_image/      # Product images — committed into repo (synced on build)
```

## Git repository and deployment
- **Repository root** must be the monorepo root (the folder that contains `website/`, `scripts/`, `.github/`, `base44_product_image/`, and `raw_catalog/`). Commit and **push from that root** so GitHub sees the full tree.
- **Do not** treat `website/` or `website/absolute-astronaut/` as **submodules** or leave a nested `.git` inside them. Submodule gitlinks (`160000` mode) break CI checkout, hide `package-lock.json`, and cause `git`/cache failures on Actions.
- **Build on CI:** Node **22.x**; `npm ci` and `npm run build` in `website/absolute-astronaut/`. `prebuild` runs `scripts/sync-public-assets.js` — requires checkout of the whole repo.
- **Astro config:** `website/absolute-astronaut/astro.config.mjs` defaults to `site: https://www.indahmachine.com` and `base: /` for local builds. CI sets **`ASTRO_SITE`** and **`ASTRO_BASE`** so assets and sitemap match `https://<owner>.github.io` and project-page `/repo/` vs user-site `/` as appropriate.

## Product Families (3 categories)
- **Alternator:** UCW, TZH, TZH-N, T2W3, T2W3-N, Mecc Alte, Brushless
- **Electric Motor:** MECC Y2/Y23, YJS, Y/YR, YPTZ/YPTQ
- **Power Press:** J23/JC23

## Data Rules
- `raw_catalog/` PDFs are the **source of truth** — never trust `product_input/` CSVs without validation
- Show `technical_specifications` only — **never** render `dimension_specifications` on any page
- Buyers download the PDF catalog to get dimension data
- Y/YR series has no PDF — omit the download button for this product only
- All images and PDFs are committed into the repo (no external GitHub raw or Supabase URLs)

## Strict Data Quality Gate (must pass before publish)
- Mandatory fields per product: `id`, `name`, `family`, `series`, `technical_specifications`, `image_path`
- `pdf_path` is mandatory for all products except Y/YR
- Normalize technical keys where available: `kW/kVA`, `Voltage`, `Frequency`, `RPM`
- No duplicate `id` values and no duplicate `model` values within the same series
- 0 broken local asset links (`image_path`, `pdf_path`)
- Block release if any gate fails

## Translation QA (best-judgment workflow)
- Auto-translate EN → ID, then manually review
- Review priority: Home/About/Contact → family pages → product details
- Preserve all technical units/symbols in translation (`kW`, `kVA`, `V`, `Hz`, `RPM`)
- Keep terminology consistent across pages

